# Prisma Conventions

## Schema Design
- Use `uuid` for all primary keys (`@default(uuid())`)
- Include `createdAt` and `updatedAt` on every model
- Use enums for fixed value sets (RiskTier, ComplianceStatus)
- Add database indexes on frequently queried columns
- Use `@@map` for snake_case table names, camelCase in Prisma

## Relationships
- Always define both sides of relations
- Use cascade delete only where semantically correct
- Soft-delete for compliance data (add `deletedAt DateTime?`)

## Queries
- Always use `select` to limit returned fields
- Use `include` sparingly — prefer separate queries for complex joins
- Wrap multi-table writes in `$transaction`
- Use `createMany` for bulk inserts

## Migrations
- Name migrations descriptively: `add-risk-tier-to-ai-systems`
- Never edit a deployed migration — create a new one
- Test migrations against production-like data volumes
- Back up database before running migrations in production

## Multi-tenancy
- Every model with user data must have `organizationId`
- All queries must filter by `organizationId` from auth context
- Create middleware to enforce tenant isolation
